{{Infobox software | title = AnTuTu | name = AnTuTu | logo = [[File:AnTuTu logo.png|frameless|middle|270px]] | logo alt = | logo caption = | screenshot = | screenshot alt = | caption = | collapsible = <!-- Any text here will collapse the screenshot --> | developer = | discontinued = <!-- Set to yes if software is discontinued, otherwise omit --> | ver layout = <!-- simple (default) or stacked --> | latest release version = 7.0 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2018|02|df=yes/no}} | status = Active | programming language = | operating system = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[Windows]] | platform = ARM | language = English | language count = <!-- Number only --> | language footnote = | genre = Benchmark (computing) | license = | alexa = | website = {{URL|http://antutu.com/}} | AsOf = }}
'''AnTuTu''' ({{zh|c=安兔兔|p=ĀnTùTu}}) is a Chinese software benchmarking tool commonly used to benchmark phones and devices.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.antutu.ABenchMark&hl=en|title=AnTuTu Benchmark - Android Apps on Google Play|author=AnTuTu|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/antutu-benchmark-measure/|title=What Does AnTuTu Benchmark Actually Measure?|author=Chris Hoffman|work=MakeUseOf}}</ref>
==Operations== The company developing the software is based in [[Chaoyang District, Beijing]],<ref>{{cite web|title=About Us|url=http://www.antutu.com/about.shtml|website=Official website of AnTuTu|accessdate=20 February 2016|language=Chinese|quote=地址：北京朝阳区朝阳北路237号复星国际中心20层 (Address: 20th Floor, Fosun International Centre, No. 237 Chaoyang North Road, Chaoyang District, Beijing)}}</ref> and was cofounded by Chinese entrepreneurs Shào Yīng (邵英)<ref>{{cite web|author1=卓克|title=重新定义跑分意义 安兔兔6.0版本发布|url=http://www.pcpop.com/doc/1/1230/1230943.shtml|website=PCPOP.com|accessdate=29 February 2016|date=18 November 2015|quote=安兔兔的创始人邵英介绍：在之前版本的积累中，这款软件已经在200多个国家使用，总用户超过2亿... (AnTuTu's founder Shao Ying said, through the previous versions of the software, it had been used in more than 200 countries, with the total user count over 200 million...)}}</ref> and Liáng Bīn (梁斌).<ref>{{cite web|author1=Hobo C|title=从手机跑分到数据服务，专访安兔兔创始人梁斌 (From smartphone benchmarking to data services, an interview with AnTuTu founder Liang Bin)|url=http://www.pcdigest.com/2014/05/antutu/|website=PCDigest.com|accessdate=29 February 2016|date=5 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305171512/http://www.pcdigest.com/2014/05/antutu/|archive-date=2016-03-05|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
==Circumvention== The AnTuTu benchmark is so common that hardware manufacturers have taken to cheating on the benchmark which makes the benchmark unreliable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://appleinsider.com/articles/13/10/03/rampant-cheating-by-android-knockoffs-prompts-antutu-to-launch-new-benchmark|title=Rampant cheating by Android knockoffs prompts AnTuTu to launch new benchmark|date=3 October 2013|work=AppleInsider}}</ref><ref name="antutu.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.antutu.com/view.shtml?id=7242|title=To Against Cheating Benchmark AnTuTu Release AnTuTu X Benchmark|publisher=}}</ref> In response to this cheating AnTuTu has created a new benchmark, called AnTuTu X, which makes it more difficult for manufacturers to cheat.<ref name="antutu.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id%3Dcom.emobile.flashlight%26hl%3Den |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-11-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224142503/https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.emobile.flashlight&hl=en |archivedate=2014-12-24 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://phandroid.com/2013/10/07/antutu-x-benchmark/|title=AnTuTu X Benchmark prevents manufacturer cheating|author=Chris Chavez|date=7 October 2013|work=Phandroid - Android News and Reviews}}</ref>
