[[Image:Canadian almanc.jpg|upright|thumb|''Canadian Global Almanac'']]
The '''''Canadian Global Almanac''''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] reference book containing a large collection of facts and statistics.  It grew out of the American ''[[World Almanac and Book of Facts]]'' when in 1986 an all-Canadian version was published, edited by [[John Filion]] and published by Susan Yates.  [[John Robert Columbo]] later became its editor.  While it was being published, a new edition was released each year in November. The almanac has not been published since 2005.

