{{orphan|date=March 2017}} {{italic}} The '''''Kanmiu Buque Qieyun''''' (刊謬補缺切韻) by Wang Renxu (王仁昫), which was published in 706, is the oldest extant [[China|Chinese]] [[rime dictionary]]. For many centuries believed lost, a copy was found at the imperial palace in [[Beijing]] in 1947. Lóng 1968 published an eye copy with annotations. Zhou 1983: 434-527 includes a facsimile of the original, which unfortunately is not very legible.
==Works cited== * {{citation | chapter = The ''Qièyùn'' manuscripts from Dūnhuáng | given = François | surname = Bottéro | pages = 33–48 | title = Studies in Chinese Manuscripts: From the Warring States Period to the 20th Century | editor-given = Imre | editor-surname = Galambos | editor-link = Imre Galambos | location = Budapest | publisher = Eötvös Loránd University | year = 2013 | isbn = 978-963-284-326-1 | url = http://shahon.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Galambos-2013-ed.-Studies-in-Chinese-manuscripts.pdf | postscript = . }}
* {{citation | title = 唐寫全本王仁昫刊謬補缺切韻校箋 Táng xiě quánběn Wáng Rénxù Kānmiù bǔquē Qièyùn jiào jiān. [Notes on the 刊謬補缺切韻 Kānmiù bǔquē Qièyùn by 王仁煦 Wáng Rénxù, written in the Táng dynasty.] | publisher = Xiānggǎng Zhōngwén dàxué 香港中文大學. | year = 1968 | author = Lóng Yǔchún 龍宇純 | location = Xiānggǎng 香港 }}
* {{citation | title = 唐五代韻書集存 Táng wǔdài yùnshū jícún [Collected rime books of the Tang and Five Dynasties | publisher = Zhōnghuá shūjú 中華書局 | year = 1983 | author = Zhōu Zǔmó 周祖謨 }}
