{{italic title}}
{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
'''''Lancashire Rock''''' is the official guidebook to rock climbing in [[Lancashire]]. Originally put together in 1969 by Les Ainsworth and supporting volunteers, there have since been seven revisions to the guidebook. The guidebook is now under the control of the [[British Mountaineering Council]], and the latest revision contains some 6,600 [[climbing]] routes either in a [[quarry]] or on a [[cliff|crag]] and making it one of the biggest climbing guidebooks in the [[UK]].

==External links==
*[http://www.lancashirerock.co.uk/ ''Lancashire Rock'' Website]

